    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>\n                  The Roborovski dwarf hamster\n                  <jats:italic>Phodopus roborovskii</jats:italic>\n                  belongs to the\n                  <jats:italic>Phodopus</jats:italic>\n                  genus, one of seven within\n                  <jats:italic>Cricetinae</jats:italic>\n                  subfamily. Like other rodents such as mice, rats or ferrets, hamsters can be important animal models for a range of diseases. Whereas the Syrian hamster from the genus\n                  <jats:italic>Mesocricetus</jats:italic>\n                  is now widely used as a model for mild to moderate COVID-19, Roborovski dwarf hamster show a severe to lethal course of disease upon infection with the novel human coronavirus SARS-CoV-2.\n                </jats:p>",
